</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1398,885,981]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Shape (from 
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley &amp; Dendy" box="[351,630,885,911]" firstAuthor="Ridley" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 275" refId="ref24197" refString="Ridley S. O. &amp; Dendy A. 1887. Report on the Monaxonida collected by H. M. S. ' Challenger' during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. ' Challenger ', 1873 - 1876, Zoology 20 (59): 1 - 275." type="journal article" year="1887">Ridley &amp; Dendy 1887</bibRefCitation>
): two small, massive encrustations, largest is 
<quantity box="[1194,1279,885,911]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="cm" value="2.9">2.9 cm</quantity>
in lateral expansion, 
<quantity box="[324,405,920,946]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="cm" value="1.6">1.6 cm</quantity>
thick, color pale greyish (in alcohol). A single oscule. Surface shaggy. Consistency soft, brittle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1020,1117]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
SKELETON. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1841" box="[318,435,1020,1046]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,435,1020,1046]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Haliclona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like, confuse, anisotropic, with primary lines consisting of 1–4 spicules, single spicules interconnecting at all angles, but mostly rectangular, no spongin visible. No special ectosomal arrangement of skeleton and spicules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1156,1217]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
OXEAS (
<figureCitation box="[280,362,1156,1182]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Haliclona (Flagellia) flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886) subgen. et comb. nov., holotype, fragment of BMNH 1887.5.2.252, from Marion Island, South Indian Ocean, SEM images of the spicules. A. Oxea. A 1. Detail of one of the apices. B–C. Large category of flagellosigmas (I). C 1. Detail of long ending of large flagellosigma. C 2. Detail of short ending of large flagellosigma. D–E. Small flagellosigmas (II). F. Sigmas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
A–A1). Slightly curved, fat, cigar-shaped, gradually pointed, 340– 
<emphasis box="[1146,1190,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">389</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1198,1213,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">1</emphasis>
–420 × 8– 
<emphasis box="[1332,1361,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">15</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1369,1384,1156,1182]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">1</emphasis>
– 18 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1257,1495]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
FLAGELLOSIGMAS (
<figureCitation box="[396,479,1257,1283]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Haliclona (Flagellia) flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886) subgen. et comb. nov., holotype, fragment of BMNH 1887.5.2.252, from Marion Island, South Indian Ocean, SEM images of the spicules. A. Oxea. A 1. Detail of one of the apices. B–C. Large category of flagellosigmas (I). C 1. Detail of long ending of large flagellosigma. C 2. Detail of short ending of large flagellosigma. D–E. Small flagellosigmas (II). F. Sigmas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
B–E). Elongated, elliptical, larger strongly asymmetrical, smaller less so and less elliptical, more ovoid. Curvature of long ending shortly rounded, no upturned hook, curvature of short ending shallow, in a wide size range, suggesting two overlapping size categories but subtly distinguishable by shape. Larger (I) (
<figureCitation box="[617,696,1362,1388]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Haliclona (Flagellia) flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886) subgen. et comb. nov., holotype, fragment of BMNH 1887.5.2.252, from Marion Island, South Indian Ocean, SEM images of the spicules. A. Oxea. A 1. Detail of one of the apices. B–C. Large category of flagellosigmas (I). C 1. Detail of long ending of large flagellosigma. C 2. Detail of short ending of large flagellosigma. D–E. Small flagellosigmas (II). F. Sigmas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
B–C) with length of long ending 82– 
<emphasis box="[1125,1154,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">96</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1162,1177,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</emphasis>
–102 μm, length of short ending 50– 
<emphasis box="[388,417,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">60</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[425,440,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">6</emphasis>
–75 μm, width 50– 
<emphasis box="[666,695,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">60</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[703,718,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</emphasis>
–73 μm, thickness 2.5– 
<emphasis box="[994,1009,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1016,1031,1398,1424]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">8</emphasis>
–3 μm. Smaller (II) (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1359,1398,1424]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Haliclona (Flagellia) flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886) subgen. et comb. nov., holotype, fragment of BMNH 1887.5.2.252, from Marion Island, South Indian Ocean, SEM images of the spicules. A. Oxea. A 1. Detail of one of the apices. B–C. Large category of flagellosigmas (I). C 1. Detail of long ending of large flagellosigma. C 2. Detail of short ending of large flagellosigma. D–E. Small flagellosigmas (II). F. Sigmas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
D– E) with length of long ending 45– 
<emphasis box="[588,617,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">54</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[625,640,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">6</emphasis>
–66 μm, length of short ending 33– 
<emphasis box="[1056,1085,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">39</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1093,1108,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">8</emphasis>
–48 μm, width 33– 
<emphasis box="[1332,1361,1433,1459]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">41</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1369,1384,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">5</emphasis>
– 46 μm, thickness 1– 
<emphasis box="[426,441,1468,1494]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">1</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[448,463,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">7</emphasis>
–2 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[189,1399,1533,1559]" box="[189,1399,1533,1559]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
NORMAL SIGMAS (
<figureCitation box="[384,487,1533,1559]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[189,1399,607,1817]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 11. Haliclona (Flagellia) flagellifera (Ridley &amp; Dendy, 1886) subgen. et comb. nov., holotype, fragment of BMNH 1887.5.2.252, from Marion Island, South Indian Ocean, SEM images of the spicules. A. Oxea. A 1. Detail of one of the apices. B–C. Large category of flagellosigmas (I). C 1. Detail of long ending of large flagellosigma. C 2. Detail of short ending of large flagellosigma. D–E. Small flagellosigmas (II). F. Sigmas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
). A single size category, tips slightly incurved, 31– 
<emphasis box="[1080,1109,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">39</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1116,1131,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">6</emphasis>
–53 × 1.5– 
<emphasis box="[1257,1272,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1279,1294,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">2</emphasis>
